HEADWORD: Adown
<hw>A*down"</hw> <pr>(<?/)</pr>, <pos>adv.</pos> <ety>[OE.
<ets>adun</ets>, <ets>adoun</ets>, <ets>adune</ets>. AS. <ets>of
d⟦umac⟧ne</ets> off the hill. See <er>Down</er>.]</ety> <def>From a
higher to a lower situation; downward; down, to or on the ground.</def>
<mark>[Archaic]</mark> ⟦ldquo⟧Thrice did she sink
<xex>adown</xex>.⟦rdquo⟧ <rj><au>Spenser.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
